From: Fabian Frederick <fabf@skynet.be>
Date: Sat, 25 Apr 2015 11:34:29 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 0362/1077] drm/i915: use ERR_CAST instead of ERR_PTR/PTR_ERR

commit 0b6cc18810cfa958985602ab1849b647250deb0f upstream.

Inspired by scripts/coccinelle/api/err_cast.cocci

Signed-off-by: Fabian Frederick <fabf@skynet.be>
Reviewed-by: Jani Nikula <jani.nikula@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Daniel Vetter <daniel.vetter@ffwll.ch>
Signed-off-by: Pengyu Ma <pengyu.ma@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_drv.h | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_drv.h b/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_drv.h
index da37164..8938d99 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_drv.h
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_drv.h
@@ -1420,7 +1420,7 @@ intel_atomic_get_crtc_state(struct drm_atomic_state *state,
 	struct drm_crtc_state *crtc_state;
 	crtc_state = drm_atomic_get_crtc_state(state, &crtc->base);
 	if (IS_ERR(crtc_state))
-		return ERR_PTR(PTR_ERR(crtc_state));
+		return ERR_CAST(crtc_state);
 
 	return to_intel_crtc_state(crtc_state);
 }
